It's called Joining the Army.

55:32.233 --> 55:34.416
It might give you some idea.

55:34.818 --> 55:36.921
since I understand you like to read.

55:37.943 --> 55:41.208
But really I never saw myself in the Army at all.

55:41.509 --> 55:47.278
I always thought of myself as a guy who likes to write a lot.

55:48.360 --> 55:52.887
But I remember it was the summer after my high school graduation.

55:53.589 --> 55:54.330
Which was what year?

55:54.350 --> 55:56.213
2003.

55:56.433 --> 56:00.640
I spent the summer down in Texas.

56:00.957 --> 56:03.459
trying to sell bug spray.

56:03.479 --> 56:05.421
I had never really lived away from my parents.

56:05.481 --> 56:06.502
That was my first attempt.

56:07.523 --> 56:09.305
And it wasn't a particularly encouraging one.

56:09.966 --> 56:11.507
And home again is where?

56:12.008 --> 56:13.950
Pocatello, Idaho.

56:14.330 --> 56:23.359
So I came back and I visited the school just before the semester started, my first semester of college.

56:24.200 --> 56:29.445
And I ran into another person who went through a Marine boot camp.

56:30.134 --> 56:33.618
And he was all, you gotta go Marines, you gotta go Marines.

56:34.500 --> 56:40.047
And he told me that, you know, you could be a writer in the military and that interested me.

56:42.189 --> 56:49.539
And I got a job writing for my college newspaper.

56:50.180 --> 56:53.424
And I guess I was probably the youngest one that ever hired for that.

56:54.605 --> 56:56.648
But I got bored with it.

56:57.083 --> 57:04.995
And I thought, you know, it would be interesting to develop my writing career in a different way.

57:06.417 --> 57:08.140
And so I considered the military thing.

57:10.363 --> 57:19.817
And I talked to a recruiter, and he kept trying to show me as a petroleum supply specialist that I'm like, it's not happening, man.

57:20.438 --> 57:26.047
And I told him I wasn't going to sign a contract until he could guarantee me 46-foot best, which is a very rare MOS.

57:27.309 --> 57:29.392
And he got desperate enough, and he did.

57:30.574 --> 57:33.678
I got it, and I was lucky because there was only one slot left in the country.

57:36.042 --> 57:38.185
So I went to basic training.

57:38.205 --> 57:40.469
I hated basic training.

57:42.051 --> 57:43.173
AIT was a little better.

57:43.614 --> 57:44.815
AIT is what?

57:44.836 --> 57:45.557
That's what they do.

57:45.677 --> 57:49.062
It's like you go to your basic training, which is just general soldier skills.

57:49.463 --> 57:52.206
And AIT is like where they teach you specifically your job.

57:53.867 --> 57:54.988
And where did you go?

57:55.909 --> 57:57.090
Fort Meade, Maryland.

57:57.190 --> 57:57.491
Oh, yeah.

57:57.811 --> 57:59.593
Well, that's where the information school is.

57:59.653 --> 58:01.054
That's where I went to.

58:01.355 --> 58:06.580
I was a graduate of the Defense Information School when I was in Fort Arizona.

58:09.202 --> 58:09.542
Right.

58:09.803 --> 58:14.427
So did you realize that you probably would be, or that you undoubtedly would be going on active duty?

58:14.647 --> 58:17.310
I had no illusions about that.

58:18.100 --> 58:19.262
It was 2004.

58:20.263 --> 58:21.445
The war was going on.

58:21.465 --> 58:27.014
The war had been going on for eight months when I signed the contract, so I knew there was going to be here.

58:27.034 --> 58:27.494
You did know?

58:28.035 --> 58:28.175
Mm-hmm.

58:28.195 --> 58:29.217
Yeah.

58:29.638 --> 58:33.403
And that didn't play any factor?

58:33.424 --> 58:40.935
It actually encouraged me because it may sound weird because it's just so not like me.

58:41.371 --> 58:55.893
I realized there are millions of people out there who like books and like writing and like the same things I do, but I thought I might be in danger of trapping myself into being sort of closed-minded.

58:56.074 --> 58:59.298
Not really closed-minded, but having a very narrow range of experiences.

59:00.500 --> 59:09.454
I decided it was early enough in my life I could change that by forcing myself to do something very out of character, like joining the military.

59:09.788 --> 59:14.212
How long do you see yourself going with it?

59:14.232 --> 59:15.673
I'm going to pitch for it.

59:16.194 --> 59:18.456
My contract is until April 2012.

59:18.496 --> 59:18.976
2012?

59:20.778 --> 59:21.058
Yeah.

59:21.799 --> 59:28.265
So you expect to be in uniform for the next six years?

59:28.445 --> 59:31.467
I mean, really?

59:31.487 --> 59:32.188
Really?

59:32.268 --> 59:33.369
That's a long time.

59:33.509 --> 59:34.210
I'm in the reserve.

59:34.830 --> 59:37.753
Would you be on active duty for the next six years?

59:38.645 --> 59:39.226
No.

59:39.246 --> 59:47.393
I'll be in the reserve, but they can call me up basically any time within that time frame.

